	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64553043"><p>I'd suggest to new users to understand commands before copying/pasting them. Or at least to take them from known reputable sources.<br>man [command] allows you to read the manual of that command. For example man sudo.</p><p>Install programs from the package manager of your distribution whenever possible, it's faster, safer and better.<br>Make sure you double check the trustiness of a program you've downloaded from a website before running it as root.</p><p>Don't run anything as root if not absolutely necessary.</p><p>systemd is the ini<span class="substr"> </span></p></div>
