</span>
		</div>
	</div>
	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64553413"><p>Text mode, all the way.</p><p>By all means use the GUI to open many terminal windows (tiled or not) in which to run VIM or Emacs and to compile and run. You can graduate to screen or tmux later on.<br>If you are coding, the GUI is a distraction.</p><p>Then, whenever you're debugging something on an SSH session to something remote, you won't be clicking around looking for the IDE. You will be prepared and you will know what to do.</p></div>
	</div>

